<a id="comment-60700"></a>
<article class="comment comment-by-anonymous even  clearfix" about="/comment/60700#comment-60700" typeof="sioc:Post sioct:Comment">
  
      <header class="comment-header">
              <h3 property="dc:title" class="comment-title">I use cabbage instead of</h3>
                      </header>
  
      <footer class="submitted">
                  <p class="author-datetime">Submitted by Elizabeth Vongvisith on October 7, 2011 - 11:18pm</p>
    </footer>
  
  <div class="comment-content">
    <span rel="sioc:reply_of" resource="/recipe/bella-cullens-colcannon" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden view-mode-full"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded">
<p>I use cabbage instead of kale, and also add a couple of sliced leeks instead of thyme. Irish butter is best for this, and Dublin's Irish cheddar for grating and melting on top, under the broiler.</p>
</div></div></div>  </div>

  
  </article>
