<article class="comment comment-by-anonymous odd  clearfix" about="/comment/60395#comment-60395" typeof="sioc:Post sioct:Comment">
  
      <header class="comment-header">
              <h3 property="dc:title" class="comment-title">My version:sub buttermilk for</h3>
                      </header>
  
      <footer class="submitted">
                  <p class="author-datetime">Submitted by Katherine Koepke on March 24, 2010 - 9:50pm</p>
    </footer>
  
  <div class="comment-content">
    <span rel="sioc:reply_of" resource="/recipe/bella-cullens-colcannon" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden view-mode-full"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded">
<p>My version:sub buttermilk for milk. add salt, pepper, chive and parsley for the seasonings (omit thyme- too strong for this dish).I also like to replace some of the potato with mashed turnip or kohlrabi. Yum!</p>
</div></div></div>  </div>

  
